sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K299000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: RBS measurement device J23100 J61100 GFP
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Anderson's RBS under J23100 synthetic promoter followed by GFP_double_terminator (I13401=E0040+B0015)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: J23100 used here is part of the Anderon RBS biobrick J61100. (Anderson RBSes comes in modified vectors)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Anna Olchowik

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K299107
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: T.xbaI.G (T followed by xbaI site and additional G to behave like biobrick prefix after xbaI digest)

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K299801
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: standard biobrick scar (if next sequence does NOT start with ATG)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Anna Olchowik

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K299802
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Aactag - like a biobrick scar but first T changed to A
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
This is a virtual part useful to anyone working with Anderson's RBS library.
First nucleotide of the biobrick suffix is varies in the library, some RBSes have T, wchich results in a regular suffix, but other hace c,G or A. This Modified scar is to help in sillico assembly of the constructs that use Anderson's RBSes.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Anna Olchowik
